TITLE: Colorado Gov. Polis says abortion requires 'gut-wrenching decisions,' defends late-term procedures
SUMMARY: Colorado Gov. Jared Polis says the government should not intrude in conversations about abortion between a woman and her doctor or faith leader. Colorado recently preserved abortion rights in state law.

TITLE: Arby's manager admits to urinating into milkshake mix 'at least twice'
SUMMARY: An Arby's manager admitted to police that he urinated in Arby's milkshake mix "at least twice."

TITLE: 'Fox News Sunday' on May 15, 2022
SUMMARY: "Fox News Sunday" welcomed guests Kevin Stitt, Jared Polis and Kathy Barnette.

TITLE: Whistleblowers saying FBI targeted parents via terrorism tools ‘scary stuff’: Rep. Jordan
SUMMARY: Republican Rep. Jim Jordan called the FBI’s alleged move to target parents who protested schools' COVID policies “scary stuff” and argued that it looks like Attorney General Merrick Garland had been misleading on the topic.

TITLE: Philadelphia police offer $20K reward for info on murder suspect seen hugging victim before fatal shooting
SUMMARY: Philadelphia police are offering a $20,000 reward for information that leads to the arrest of a murder suspect who was seen on video hugging the victim before the fatal shooting last year, authorities said Friday.

TITLE: WNBPA calls on Biden, Harris to help free Brittney Griner from detention in Russia
SUMMARY: The WNBPA is pleading with the White House, President Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris to do whatever it takes to return Brittney Griner to the U.S. from Russia.

TITLE: Biden says hate ‘remains a stain on the soul of America’ after Buffalo mass shooting
SUMMARY: President Biden said hate "remains a stain on the soul of America" after an alleged white supremacist gunned down 10 people Saturday afternoon.

TITLE: Teenager shot to death at major Chicago tourist destination
SUMMARY: A 16-year-old boy was fatally shot at Chicago's "The Bean" sculpture in Millennium Park.

TITLE: Pro-choice activists in Canada, Mexico prepare for 'big influx' of Americans seeking abortions
SUMMARY: Pro-choice activists who spoke to The Hill said they are preparing for a potential “big influx” of American women crossing the Mexican and Canadian borders seeking abortions if the Supreme Court overturns Roe v. Wade.

TITLE: Gardening 101: Grow your own food as inflation maintains a historic high
SUMMARY: If you’re looking for a way to save money on grocery bills, growing your own food could be the solution that helps you out, according to Skip Bedell, who appeared on "Fox & Friends" to share tips.

TITLE: SCOTUS leak hasn't moved needle on which party Americans prefer to run Congress: Poll
SUMMARY: The leak potentially overruling Roe v. Wade has not changes the preference of voters ahead of the midterm election's, with a poll showing a tight race between Republicans and Democrats.

TITLE: NY Times editorial board says 'canceling student debt across the board' is 'a bad idea'
SUMMARY: The New York Times editorial board argued Saturday that canceling student loan debt was a "bad idea."

TITLE: 1985 cold case murder mystery solved by unlikely pair: Tennessee mom and Georgia police civilian employee
SUMMARY: A Tennessee stay at home mom and a civilian employee for a Georgia police department cracked a 1985 cold case that went unsolved for 37 years.

TITLE: NY first responders rescue driver from car that crashed into reservoir, video shows
SUMMARY: New York state police have released video showing officers and firefighters rescue a driver trapped inside a sinking car that crashed into a reservoir last week.

TITLE: Biden slammed for 'waging war' on US industry: 'We have crises erupting across our nation,' Sen. Hagerty says
SUMMARY: Sen. Bill Hagerty, R-Tenn., weighed in on the $40 billion Ukrainian aid package during an appearance on 'Sunday Morning Futures.'

TITLE: Biden administration to remove 5 terror groups from blacklist
SUMMARY: The Biden administration plans to remove five terror organizations from a federal blacklist.

TITLE: Frank Gore scores vicious knockout in pro boxing debut on his birthday
SUMMARY: Former NFL running back Frank Gore celebrated his 39th birthday Saturday by scoring a fourth-round knockout in his professional boxing debut against Yaya Olorunsola.

TITLE: Oklahoma Gov. defends strict abortion law, addresses whether 'super liberal' tribal clinics may use loophole
SUMMARY: Oklahoma Gov. Kevin Stitt pushed back against critics of his state's abortion law, which bans abortion when there is a fetal heartbeat, typically six weeks into pregnancy, while recognizing that there is a gaping loophole.

TITLE: Americans increasingly believe acceptance of trans identity has gone too far: Poll
SUMMARY: More Americans say the country has gone too far with transgender policies compared to previous polls, closing the gap with those who say society has to do more to end discrimination against transgender people.

TITLE: British intelligence says Russia has 'lost momentum,' fallen well behind Ukraine invasion schedule
SUMMARY: The British Ministry of Defence claimed that Russia has lost a full one-third of its ground combat forces committed in February and British Intelligence officials say Russia has "lost momentum" in Donbas.
